      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Most interesting race. IN NO DOUBT (4) has been freshened since having no luck in Alice last time when she shuffled back at the wrong time. Much better draw here and worth another chance. Same goes for DAD BOD (5) who drew an outside gate last time and was off the track throughout. Gassed by the corner and faded out of it. Can improve sharply. The big query is JUMPING POWER TWO (2) who surely has an interesting story about the journey. Former Victorian who had four runs for the new yard and won all four. Went for a break and had two barrier trials back in Victoria in March, then went back to the paddock. Returns again back in the Top End and on what he did in his first campaign could well just put these away. BLACK COAL (3) has been freshened since a fourth in Alice last time and can do better. LAVENDER GLORY (7) is a former Victorian expected to prove hard to beat on best figures. Watch betting.",
